<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/45111318-chip-young">Chip Young</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">In the Nature of Order, a 3-book series published in 2003-2004, he takes patterns one step further with what he calls sequences, which describe how to<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">In the Nature of Order, a 3-book series published in 2003-2004, he takes patterns one step further with what he calls sequences, which describe how to work toward patterns. The idea of patterns has also been very influential in software engineering, to the point where it is a commonly accepted way of thinking about and describing software designs and components.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
