<span id="freeTextContainer1118014705107349422">This text was invaluable to my understanding of three things: first, how to approach the programming language concepts of Lisp macros, generic types, and code generation; second, why the &quot;design patterns&quot; concept in software construction is misguided; and third, the aesthetics of Middle Eastern rugs.</span>
  <span id="freeText1118014705107349422" style="display:none">This text was invaluable to my understanding of three things: first, how to approach the programming language concepts of Lisp macros, generic types, and code generation; second, why the "design patterns" concept in software construction is misguided; and third, the aesthetics of Middle Eastern rugs.</span>
